        <td bgcolor="ivory" colspan="2" valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/03/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 10:39:39</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=14"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=7655531&M_NAME=Zlater')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=7655531&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Zlater an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=2428&FORUM_ID=53&CAT_ID=10&Forum_Title=Veeshan+Alliance+%28Raid+Forum%29&Topic_Title=Last+nights+Hate+raid%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Heya Kiddies. Thought I'd do one of my Raid recaps that I do so love to bore you with. Mostly just so everyone understands what it's like to be a raid leader.. Hmm wonder if this will fall into the category of...</P><P><h2><b><i><center><font color=red>MASTERCHOAD THEATRE!</h2></b></i></center></font id=red></P><P>Guess we'll find out as we go along!</P><P>Usual start for me. I log on in the wrong zone and start checking for clerics between 46 and 60. NONE in HATE.. WOOHOO, raid on! Check my bag, doh, only 4 magic stones.. Time for a trip to Neriak. I find everyone wants to use va-hate for our raid channel and I used that to count who was there. I LIKE THAT NEW FEATURE!! Halfway thru Neriak I find out that the Guild " Innoruuk's Hidden ones " are planning a raid to hate as well. Oh goodie, competition... crappers. Well if they can get there first, they can have it! Upon leaving Neriak, I get a tell from some IHO member saying verbatim..<BR>" Hey, were going to Hate, what are you guys doing? "<BR>My response..<BR>" Hi, were uh.. going to Hate.. "<BR>Cant remember what he typed back, something to the works of they were getting ready to port up now. Now as a raid leader, I try to work this game as fairly as possible. If someone gets claim to an area first, I will defer as in my mind, thats fair. So I answered...<BR>" Well if you can get up and established before us, I will defer "<BR>I kept running to Lavastorm to get to air Druid!<BR>By the time I was in SRO, I get a tell from the same guy, " We have one group up! ". CURSES!! Trying to foil me ehh?? Well thats why I used the word <i>established</i>. One group sitting in the corner does not a Hate raid make.. On arrival at the wizzi portal, I counted 4 IHO members hanging about. I did a /who on the person who was in tells to me.. He was in Dawnshroud.. I shook that off as it simply could have been he didnt go with the advance team. We then all rallied together to get the classes ready to go. If there werent many in Hate, we were going to go ahead. In truth however, had they had 12 people in Hate, I would have cancelled. In my mind, that would have been fair.<BR>5 min later, I get a tell from the same person " We were wiped out " ( Paraphrasing ). and a second tell " But the Companions are helping us." DOH, this could really stop us from going to Hate. On a quick check, we can find no companions in HATE!! OK this is getting fishy. I then told the person we would assist in recovery, formed 3 groups, and ported up. <BR>First group up... " PD and Companions are here "<BR>WHAT??!!!?!? THey must have been anon or something because I could not find them using conventional techniques. <BR>" Well what are they doing there? Find out how many "<BR>Not sure who sent this tell...<BR>" There are 5. The one guy just said.. Hate is camped LOA, Good day "<BR>OK that may have been just crappy English but No fricken way am I deferring for 5 people gem farming!! " NAME!!! "<BR>I got about 3 names, I chose one and sent a tell..<BR>" Hi, your holding Hate with 5 people?? "<BR>I wont post responses, needless to say the person I spoke to was not rude, but very nice about it. They just wanted the SW corner.. OK, we can deal with that...<BR>The rest of the groups ported up and we held the gatehouse for a little while. <BR>To those who were not there for the first 5 minutes in Hate, We almost wiped! Ok not really, but it sure woulda looked that way. We were at 18 people, we had one bard with us, NO enc and we have 7 mobs train the gatehouse!! The Damage group had NO CLERIC as he LD'ed but we kept our heads, split the mobs ( I DIDNT EVEN CALL IT!! THe team excersized initiative and worked the mobs EXCELLENTLY!! ). In about 8 minutes, we had the train wiped with few deaths. We got on our feet and started to work Hate!</P><P>I'm not going to go into specifics of what happened. Hates 1st floor was at least 50% clear when we got there. We took down the Maestro with only 2 deaths. THat too was a good job as we SOMEHOW got a spite on us on Maestro pull. Gooba tanked the spite the whole time and Crazi tanked the Maestr thru 3 CH's and only died about a minute before songboy did. ( had we gotten that cleric in the back sooner I think we would have done a lot better. But that was our only mis so Damn good job )<BR>Only real downside is we had to break camp before Midnight EST as people had to go. Loot was slow due to crap spawns but a few people walked away with stuff.</P><P>My hats go off to the Team. THE VA did extremly well working together last night and I am impressed to think we can consider focusing on the harder mobs and spawn points soon. I think we can consider going after an uber mob like Trak or Velketors soon! We could use the practice anyway!</P><P>OH and I do convey my appologies and sympathies to IHO. I did not mean to rush them to Hate which is probably the only reason they died on arrival. IN this particular case we just had more people ready before them. Good luck on thier next attempt!</P><P><b><i>Zlater ShadowProwler<BR>BlackGuard of the <font color=red>58th</font id=red> Circle<BR>Lost Order of Akalabeth<BR>Lord of War<BR>--------------------------------<BR></b></i><BR></font></td>

      </tr>

